The method was validated under optimal conditions per regulations of EU 2002/657/EC Decision. The standard chromatograms of THI and ASO analytes at 200 μg‧L−1 are shown in Fig. S4a. The retention times for ASO and THI were 11.87 and 14.91 min, respectively, with their separation and detection achieved within 16 min. A standard curve was plotted using eight different concentrations of mixed standard solution (4.0 μg‧L−1 to 250 μg‧L−1), as shown in Fig. S4b. Table S1 illustrates a strong linear relationship for THI and ASO within the concentration range of 4.0 μg‧L−1 to 200 μg‧L−1 and 5.0 μg·L−1 to 250 μg·L−1, respectively. The linear correlation coefficients (R

                           2
                        ) were determined to be 0.9986 and 0.9993, respectively. The limits of detection (LOD, S/N = 3) for THI and ASO were 1.33 μg·L−1 and 1.61 μg·L−1, respectively. The relative standard deviation (RSD) of the retention times for both analytes was below 0.55 %, while the RSD of peak heights was below 1.54 %.
